f=Engineering/ops/operational/skill/ops-skill-routing.md · p=ops's four skills fit together. ops department's **safety net**: ships what quinn passed (reversibly), catches what breaks (and makes teach system), keeps healthy system healthy. ops owns production; build features gate quality builders' quinn's. · h2:The shape=`platform-playbooks (dated mechanics for THIS business's stack — read by all three) \· │ \· release-discipline ──ships──> production <──keeps healthy── maintenance-hygiene \· (rollback-first)                │                          (deps/backups/baselines/expiries) \· │ breaks` · h2:Routing rules="Deploy ship rollback canary" **release-discipline** (preconditions: quinn GATE PASS locked plan), which pulls strategy/mechanics **marketplace/deployment-patterns** (rolling/blue-green/canary trade-offs, Docker, CI/CD stages, probes, readiness checklists dated snippets bind platform-playbooks). Conflicts resolve release-discipline., "Down broken users affected alert fired post-mortem" **incident-response**., "Dependencies backups baselines expiry CVE normal" **maintenance-hygiene**., "How [platform] write playbook logs" **platform-playbooks**., Host-specific steps inside ANY skill cite playbook date; undated platform claims., failed restore test incident-response (P2), register note., failed deploy verify release-discipline rolls back NOW; incident-response users hit. · h2:Handoffs=**quinn**: GATE PASS precedes ship; ops's tool calls plan-locked; post-mortems feed regression map (mandatory, written why-not)., **dev**: design flaws incidents become ADRs; recurrence mapped fragility escalates dev; platform changes ADRs before playbooks change; "rollback-ready" dev's DoD release-discipline's requirement., **dana** (when built): authors migration/data script; OPERATOR executes (Rail ops sequences, never runs them., **aegis** (when built): CVE triage above patch-level security incidents become joint., **board** (Governance): infra spend above-threshold changes gate (plan §6)., Senior authority: **Security Charter** held even mid-incident; urgency never rail exception.